com.avaje.ebean

Class Model.Finder<I,T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.avaje.ebean.Model.Find<I,T>
      • com.avaje.ebean.Model.Finder<I,T>
  • Type Parameters:
    I - type of the Id property
    T - type of the entity bean
    Enclosing class:
    Model

    public static class Model.Finder<I,T>
extends Model.Find<I,T>
    A concrete implementation of Find.

    It should be preferred to use Model.Find instead of Finder as that can use reflection to determine the class literal type of the entity bean.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Finder

        public Finder(Class<T> type)
        Create with the type of the entity bean. 
        @Entity
public class Customer extends BaseModel {

  public static final Finder<Long,Customer> find = new Finder<Long,Customer>(Customer.class);
  ...

        The preferred approach is to instead use Find as below. This approach is more DRY in that it does not require the class literal Customer.class to be passed into the constructor. 

        @Entity
public class Customer extends BaseModel {

  public static final Find<Long,Customer> find = new Find<Long,Customer>(){};
  ...
